<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--HairRaid     06-24 0177</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Hair Raid,0181</SECOND>
<HEAD>Maid Goes Out on Limb, Wins Right to Work Without Pantyhose, Shaved
Legs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WELLINGTON, New Zealand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A maid at an exclusive hotel won
her fight to work with unshaven legs and without pantyhose, the
Wellington Hotel Workers' Union said Saturday.
   Union secretary Peter Cullen said the unidentified maid at
Wellington's ritzy James Cook Hotel was threatened with suspension
unless she complied with new rules that appeared in a memo at the
same time new uniforms were issued.
   In the memo, the hotel said it insisted ``on regular leg
grooming. If you do not wish to groom your legs you will be required
to wear pantyhose.''
   The maid did not want to shave her legs or have to pay for
pantyhose, Cullen said.
   The union and hotel negotiated an agreement, and the maid will be
allowed to work without shaving her legs or wearing pantyhose, the
union said.
   James Cook duty manager Olivia Martin said staff were asked to
wear pantyhose but no action was to be taken against those who
refused.
