<SECOND>AM-Germany-China,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Report: Chinese Diplomat Seeks Political Asylum in West Germany</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-China, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Chinese diplomat based in communist East Berlin
has sought political asylum in West Germany, West German television
reported Saturday.
   The ZDF television network said the diplomat traveled to West
Berlin and told officials that the measures used by the government
in Beijing against pro-democracy protesters prompted him to abandon
his post.
   It did not identify the diplomat.
   Communist East Germany has supported the crackdown on the
pro-democracy movement in China. Several demonstrators have been
detained in East Berlin while attempting to deliver protest letters
to officials in the Chinese Embassy.
   West Germany's Parliament on Friday demanded that the Chinese
government cease executions and mass arrests that have followed the
crackdown.
   The country's top-lawmaking body, the Bundestag, also called on
the West German government to suspend further capital development
assistance to China.
